import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'])
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the overall trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['daily_return'], bins=30, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Daily Return')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily returns for the S&P 500 index?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['price'], data['daily_return'])
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Daily Return')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the correlation between the 'price' and 'daily_return' fields?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    mean_daily_return = data['daily_return'].mean()
    plt.bar('Mean Daily Return', mean_daily_return)
    plt.axhline(mean_daily_return, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {mean_daily_return:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.title("What is the average daily return of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
